node.text:
By @grillhunters 
.
Have you ever had a grilled romaine salad before? If not, you’re in for a unique and delicious smoky surprise.

Here’s a list of ingredients for the marinade and salad. Full recipe with instruction is on the blog.

// Garlic & herbs marinade //
- 3/4 cup olive oil
- 1 lemon juice
- 1 tbsp basil, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp chives, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp rosemary, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp parsley, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp lemon zest
- 3 garlic cloves, minced
- 1/2 tsp chili powder
- 1 tsp salt
- 1 tsp black pepper

// Grilles Romaine Salad //
- 1 heart romaine lettuce cut in half lengthwise 
- ½ cup Parmesan cheese flakes
- 4 slice bacon grilled and crispy
- 4 tbsp olive oil extra virgin
- 1 tbsp kosher salt
- 1 lemon juice
- 1 tsp back pepper
- ½ lemon zest

#NomadGrills #grillhunters #grilledlettuce #grilledsalad #vealchop #grilledvealchops #smokedveal

node.text:
from Scratch! 🇲🇦😍🍆🍅🔥
This dish is a must and the flavors are amazing!
🕌: Fez, Morocco
🎥: @foodyfetish #foodyfetishoriginal 
Tag a Friend that would love this dish!👇🏼
.

Ingredients
* 1 large eggplant (peeled and chopped*)
* 4 large tomatoes (peeled, seeded and chopped)
* 3 cloves of garlic (finely chopped or pressed)
* 1/3 cup chopped fresh cilantro and parsley (mixed)
* 1 tablespoon paprika
* 1 tablespoon cumin
* 1 1/2 teaspoons salt
* 1/8 teaspoon cayenne pepper (optional)
* 1/4 cup olive oil
* 1/3 cup water
* Small wedge of lemon (optional)

To Make the Zaalouk:
* Mix all ingredients in a large, deep skillet or pot. Cover and simmer over medium to medium-high heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Adjust the heat if necessary to avoid burning the zaalouk.  Use a spoon or potato masher to crush and blend the tomatoes and eggplant. If you like, a small wedge of lemon can be added to the pan at this time. Continue simmering, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until the liquids are reduced and the zaalouk can be stirred into a heap in the center of the pan.

node.text:
🍗🍣 What’s your favourite protein?
*Swipe for some vegetarian options too🌱:) by @nessasphere
⠀
When it comes to protein sources, Its best to vary throughout the week 🍽✔️
Different sources of protein contain different essential vitamins and nutrients. Red meat is rich in vitamin B12 and iron whereas fish like salmon or sardines are high in omega-3 fatty acids.
⠀
Eating too much of the same foods over and over again not only gets boring but can lead to dietary deficiencies.
⠀
Chicken or turkey 🍗
white meat is the leanest choice, but I wouldn't give up on dark meat if you skip the skin. Both chicken and turkey give you about 25 grams of high-quality protein, along with B vitamins and selenium. Chicken is also easy to cook.
⠀
Beef 🥩
lean meat delivers up to 27 grams of protein, along with a healthy dose of iron, zinc, vitamin B12 and numerous other nutrients.
⠀
Pork 🍖
contains branched-chain amino acids BCAAs which are key in supporting muscle recovery. If you choose lean pork it is not that high in fat.
⠀
Shrimp 🍤
a type of seafood very low in fat, 0.3g per 100g and gives you 24 grams of protein. It is rich in vitamin D, niacin, selenium and vitamin B12. Moreover, they contain antioxidants such as astaxanthin, which reduces inflammation and oxidative damage.
⠀
Cod 🐟
a great source of vitamins B3, B6 and B12, as well as omega 3, all provide benefits for heart health. Additionally, cod contains selenium, magnesium and potassium. it is packed with protein (18g), low in calories and little fat.
⠀
Salmon🐠
iron, zinc, niacin, vitamin B6 + vitamin B12, in addition to a whole host of other nutrients you need for good health. It tends to be very high in heart-healthy omega-3 fatty acids.
⠀
I recommend you vary your protein sources by incorporating fish, red meat, chicken, but also eggs + beans + vegetables + nuts keep you feeling great and covering all your dietary deficiencies. This post is by @nessasphere and she suggests to mix things up a bit also keeps your diet interesting + let you perform at your best 🤗 
Nutrition values 100g
🍤🥓🍗🍳🍤🍗

#protein #meat #salmon #chicken #calories #weightloss #diet #healthychoices #fish #gains #nutrition #healthyfood #chef

Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness for the best nutrition, mindset and fitness tips
.
Broccoli + Fresh Corn + Bacon Salad 🥦🌽🥓

This one is an ABSOLUTE CROWD PLEASER! 🤤

If you're planning a backyard get-together this weekend, then this lil' beauty *must* be apart of your menu!
By @cleanfoodcrush 

Ingredients
* 2 medium heads of broccoli
* 2 large carrots
* 2 cups fresh or frozen organic corn
* ½ cup raisins, or golden raisins
* ½ cup pecans, or nut of choice, roughly chopped
* 6-8 slices of nitrate free bacon, cooked, crispy, and crumbled
* ½ cup shredded cheese of your choice 

For the dressing:
* 1 cup plain Greek yogurt
* 2 Tbsp raw honey
* 2 Tbsps Dijon mustard
* 2 tsps apple cider vinegar
* 3 Tbsps sweet onion, minced 

Instructions
1. Whisk all of your dressing ingredients together really well, in a glass bowl and refrigerate until ready to use. 

2. Thoroughly rinse your broccoli under cold running water to remove any dirt. Allow excess moisture to drain on a kitchen towel. 

3. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Drop shucked ears of corn into your boiling water and steam just 2-3 minutes. Remove from water to a large bowl and allow to cool a few minutes until you can handle them. Cut kernels off of cobs. 

4. Chop the broccoli into very small florets, all roughly the same bite-sized pieces, then place in a large bowl. 

5. Peel and shred your carrots. 

6. Add in the shredded carrots, corn, raisins and pecans into the broccoli bowl. 

7. Drizzle your prepared dressing on top and toss really well. 

8. Crumble the cooked bacon on top and sprinkle with cheese, stir well and serve immediately, or place back in the fridge, covered, for up to an hour before you plan to serve. 

9. Store any leftover salad in an air-tight container for up to 2 days. 

10. Enjoy!

#healthyeating #healthyeats #bbq #salad

node.text:
This post goes out to all my apple lovers around the world 🍎🍏 Let me just say I am one of them 🙋‍♀️…Made by @meowmeix
.⠀⠀⠀⁠
Honestly, I can believe how many different varieties there are out there! This isn’t even all of them. I encourage you to try them all and find the varieties you fall in love with.⠀⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⠀⁠
Apples aren’t just delicious, they’re also very nutritious. Apples are packed with water and fiber which both can help you feel fuller for longer. Additionally, apples contain vitamin C, polyphenols, and a type of fiber called pectin that acts as a prebiotic, meaning it feeds your good gut bacteria. To get the most benefits, eat the whole apple, both the skin and flesh.⠀⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⠀⁠
Curious if you have a favorite apple? It’s almost too hard for me to pick.⠀⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⠀l
.⁠⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠
